to the editor your dec 1 automobiles section article about the benefits and risks of air bags in automobiles raises an important issue auto manufacturers withhold data regarding air bag performance to the detriment of consumers and researchers the author of one important comparison study dr maria segui gomez explained in the article that she could not analyze differences in injury and fatality data caused by air bag design because manufacturers keep these details of designs secret as you point out air bags not only save lives but can actually cause harm to certain passengers like smaller women and children particularly in low speed crashes the new findings make even clearer the need for public access to this information so consumers can choose the best air bag design for their needs joan claybrook washington dec 1 2000 the writer the president of public citizen was administrator of the national highway traffic safety administration 1977 81

